07:56.651 --> 07:58.777
I've seen that in movies.

07:58.779 --> 08:00.737
Some gangster with a poker game,

08:00.739 --> 08:03.615
and we come through the
doors with shotguns.

08:03.617 --> 08:05.910
And nobody can call
the cops because,

08:05.912 --> 08:08.578
it's all illegal anyway.

08:08.580 --> 08:10.707
And you know this gangster
with the poker game.

08:11.876 --> 08:13.875
No but we can find one.

08:13.877 --> 08:16.377
I mean we know
people we can ask.

08:16.379 --> 08:18.507
Come on, you're not
thinking creatively.

08:19.508 --> 08:21.382
There's money out there Fred.

08:21.384 --> 08:22.675
So much of it.

08:22.677 --> 08:25.930
And it's just sitting
in people's pockets.

08:25.932 --> 08:28.015
Let's figure out
how we can take it.

08:32.770 --> 08:34.437
You know my grandfather
was real creative.

08:34.438 --> 08:37.398
He used to robbed banks and,

08:37.400 --> 08:39.609
bars and restaurants, pharmacies,
whatever you name it.

08:39.611 --> 08:40.527
He's famous.

08:40.529 --> 08:41.861
In newspapers and everything.

08:41.864 --> 08:42.654
Nuh uh.

08:42.655 --> 08:44.280
Yeah he is.

08:44.282 --> 08:46.324
Boe Carroll.

08:46.326 --> 08:48.993
He killed a lady a
year before I was born.

08:48.995 --> 08:51.746
He ran her over in his car,

08:51.748 --> 08:54.541
leaving a smash and grab
actually at a car dealership.

08:54.543 --> 08:56.709
They gave him life for that.

08:56.711 --> 08:57.585
You're making it up.

08:57.587 --> 08:58.378
I'm not.

08:58.380 --> 08:59.170
Boe Carroll.

08:59.172 --> 08:59.963
Grandpa Boe.

08:59.965 --> 09:00.967
Look it up.

09:01.801 --> 09:03.383
Look it up.

09:03.385 --> 09:04.926
Boe Carroll.

09:04.928 --> 09:07.095
A celebrity in the family.

09:07.097 --> 09:09.639
Why haven't you
mentioned him before?

09:09.641 --> 09:12.725
Not exactly something
most people are proud of.

09:12.727 --> 09:14.102
They have internet.

09:14.104 --> 09:15.019
Don't us it.

09:15.021 --> 09:16.271
It's probably expensive as hell.

09:16.273 --> 09:18.147
We'll put
it on the cards.

09:18.149 --> 09:22.110
He sold robberies,
more than anything else.

09:22.112 --> 09:23.987
Find a mark, stake
it out for years.

09:23.989 --> 09:26.906
Seriously, years.

09:26.908 --> 09:29.200
He'd figure out where the
entrance and the exit were,

09:29.202 --> 09:32.203
and then pinpoint when the
place would be flush with cash.

09:32.205 --> 09:33.496
And then, when the
time was right,

09:33.498 --> 09:35.040
he'd either sell the job,

09:35.042 --> 09:38.878
or if it was real special
he'd do it himself.

09:38.880 --> 09:41.006
My dad actually
worked a lot with him.

09:42.132 --> 09:44.632
They made a real
living doing it,

09:44.634 --> 09:46.844
back in the day when you could
make a real living doing it.

09:46.846 --> 09:47.845
Here he is!

09:47.847 --> 09:48.848
Boe Carroll.

09:50.557 --> 09:52.975
He's handsome.

09:52.977 --> 09:54.267
He had my dad when
he was like nineteen,

09:54.269 --> 09:57.353
so they were more like
brothers than anything else.

09:57.355 --> 09:59.397
Fred, Freddie.

09:59.399 --> 10:00.773
Grandpa's a free man.

10:00.775 --> 10:01.774
What?

10:01.776 --> 10:02.692
Yep.

10:02.694 --> 10:04.319
There did a news story about it.

10:04.321 --> 10:05.570
Bullshit they gave him life.

10:05.572 --> 10:06.362
Yeah.

10:06.364 --> 10:07.447
Released last October.

10:07.449 --> 10:08.910
He's been out a year.

10:11.119 --> 10:12.785
Intermediate life sentence.

10:12.787 --> 10:13.829
Indeterminate.

10:13.831 --> 10:15.915
Indeterminate life sentence.

10:15.917 --> 10:18.708
I thought life in prison
meant life in prison.

10:18.710 --> 10:20.545
