long a life is?

11:16.059 --> 11:18.142
Holy shit.

11:18.144 --> 11:19.604
Boe, is that you?

11:22.649 --> 11:25.483
Cause all I can
see is an old man.

11:25.485 --> 11:26.275
It's me, Artie.

11:26.277 --> 11:28.154
I'm in here somewhere.

11:29.197 --> 11:32.032
C'mere, before I start crying.

11:41.376 --> 11:43.626
When Ann died I traded
our house for this place,

11:43.628 --> 11:45.586
and I never got around to,

11:45.588 --> 11:49.174
exactly decorating.

11:49.176 --> 11:51.551
Why'd you sell your house?

11:51.553 --> 11:54.138
It was too much to maintain.

11:54.140 --> 11:55.140
Too much room.

11:56.599 --> 11:58.266
That was Ann's house, right?

11:58.268 --> 12:00.101
The one on Glenoaks?

12:00.103 --> 12:01.394
Yeah.

12:01.396 --> 12:03.354
I took the cash from
the sale of the house,

12:03.356 --> 12:06.107
for a little retirement.

12:06.109 --> 12:07.692
Savings only go so far,

12:07.694 --> 12:10.863
and God knows the government
only helps out so much.

12:10.865 --> 12:13.031
That was her
parents house, no?

12:13.033 --> 12:15.702
I mean she grew up there.

12:17.454 --> 12:19.039
Situations change.

12:20.707 --> 12:22.081
You know,

12:22.083 --> 12:25.836
When I got all the paper
work for the parole board,

12:25.838 --> 12:28.256
and I saw your address
wasn't Glenoaks,

12:31.134 --> 12:32.134
I felt a chill.

12:34.345 --> 12:35.388
Time goes by, Boe.

12:36.306 --> 12:39.141
I don't have to tell you that.

12:39.143 --> 12:40.143
No.

12:41.145 --> 12:42.895
Anyway, look,

12:42.897 --> 12:44.897
this place is more
than enough for me,

12:44.899 --> 12:46.566
and plenty of room for a guest.

12:47.902 --> 12:49.317
You're more than welcome here.

12:49.319 --> 12:50.319
I mean it.

12:51.404 --> 12:55.450
I got to thank you
Artie, for taking me in.

12:56.994 --> 12:59.744
What we been through, come on?

12:59.746 --> 13:01.080
To be honest, it'll be
nice to have a friend,

13:01.082 --> 13:02.956
