Some, I don't know,
Pakistani family.

19:26.675 --> 19:29.468
I thought it could wait
a day, but it can't.

19:29.470 --> 19:31.845
I got to go now.

19:31.847 --> 19:33.640
Why do you have to
go to Ann's house?

19:34.600 --> 19:36.141
I gotta get something.

19:36.143 --> 19:37.143
Something I buried.

19:38.520 --> 19:39.727
Something you buried?

19:39.729 --> 19:41.604
Before I went away.

19:41.606 --> 19:44.193
In the back yard,
behind the fence.

19:45.319 --> 19:46.652
In '79?

19:53.452 --> 19:55.619
How deep are we talkin?

20:01.335 --> 20:04.585
You're still a
crazy motherfucker.

20:04.587 --> 20:06.171
All those years
of good behavior,

20:06.173 --> 20:08.631
you were just killing
time, weren't you?

20:10.593 --> 20:12.637
What else you gonna
do in jail, Arthur?

20:14.932 --> 20:17.432
I told you it'd still be there.

20:17.434 --> 20:18.936
You buried it deep enough.

20:21.396 --> 20:22.145
What you want to do,

20:22.147 --> 20:23.147
get us both locked up?

20:25.651 --> 20:26.985
No, not again.

20:28.904 --> 20:30.654
Not ever.

20:30.656 --> 20:31.656
What the fuck?

20:32.616 --> 20:33.572
Let's get some sleep.

20:33.574 --> 20:35.492
Fuck that.

20:35.494 --> 20:37.537
You're showing me what's
in there, right now.

20:40.290 --> 20:41.708
It's private, okay?

20:42.876 --> 20:43.876
Not okay.

20:45.504 --> 20:46.504
Open that thing.

20:47.965 --> 20:50.467
You ever do any time Arthur?

20:51.551 --> 20:52.759
What does that got
to do with anything?

20:52.761 --> 20:55.097
No, you've never done a day.

20:56.974 --> 20:59.558
Look I am aware,

20:59.560 --> 21:02.435
that I've been very lucky
and you got fucked over.

21:02.437 --> 21:04.145
You've never had
to take a shit,

21:04.147 --> 21:06.147
in a room the size of a closet,

21:06.149 --> 21:08.441
with another man watching you,

21:08.443 --> 21:10.193
getting ready to
take a shit himself,

21:10.195 --> 21:12.070
and you're gonna
have to watch him,

21:12.072 --> 21:12.988
or at least smell it.

21:12.990 --> 21:14.613
Cause sure you could turn away,

21:14.615 --> 21:17.077
but you have to smell it.

21:18.036 --> 21:19.036
Breath it.

21:21.206 --> 21:24.749
Boe, you can't stay here,

21:24.751 --> 21:26.876
if you don't show me
what's inside the box.

21:26.878 --> 21:30.964
26 years I waited
to dig this up.

21:30.966 --> 21:35.385
It's the only privacy I've
got left in the world.

21:35.387 --> 21:37.512
It's all I've got
left to myself.

21:37.514 --> 21:40.765
I mean 26 miserable
god damned years,

21:40.767 --> 21:43.228
I spent every night
dreaming of this box.

21:44.521 --> 21:47.105
It was out here, in the world,

21:47.107 --> 21:50.859
buried where only I knew.

21:50.861 --> 21:53.736
My ass may have belonged
to the state, but this box,

21:53.738 --> 21:56.698
buried, locked, untouched.

21:56.700 --> 21:59.828
This I could claim for myself.

22:00.912 --> 22:02.579
You speak of good behavior,

22:02.581 --> 22:04.331
oh there was lots of that.

22:04.333 --> 22:06.374
Yes sir, no ma'am.

22:06.376 --> 22:08.835
But the shameful
cocksuckery of that,

22:08.837 --> 22:11.254
was made just about
barely endurable,

22:11.256 --> 22:14.591
by being able to lay down
every night and dream,

22:14.593 --> 22:18.221
of the one place on God's earth
I could still call my own.

22:25.686 --> 22:26.730
Arthur,

22:32.361 --> 22:33.362
you're my friend,

22:35.823 --> 22:37.574
my only friend in the world,

22:39.201 --> 22:43.163
but I cannot show you
what's in this box.

22:44.874 --> 22:45.874
I will not.

22:51.838 --> 22:54.130
What about your
parole officer,

22:54.132 --> 22:55.133
you gonna show him?

22:56.301 --> 22:57.676
Cause he's gonna come over,

22:57.678 --> 22:59.177
he's gonna search
through your shit,

22:59.179 --> 23:01.847
and he's gonna see
a steel cash box,

23:01.849 --> 23:05.308
and believe me, I think he's
gonna want a peek inside.

23:05.310 --> 23:06.894
No.

23:06.896 --> 23:10.271
During the day we'll
keep it in your room.

23:10.273 --> 23:11.774
We'll lock it in your closet.

23:12.902 --> 23:15.819
At night it stays with me.

23:15.821 --> 23:17.320
What do you got in there?

23:17.322 --> 23:18.738
Some teddy bear?

23:18.740 --> 23:20.365
You wanna sleep with it?

23:20.367 --> 23:22.327
Under the pillow
if comfort allows.

23:26.248 --> 23:27.958
What am I gonna do with you?

23:29.668 --> 23:31.960
Thanks for
understanding Arthur.

23:31.962 --> 23:33.211
No I don't understand.

23:33.213 --> 23:34.213
I'm giving in.

23:35.966 --> 23:38.007
Sometimes that's what it takes.

23:44.599 --> 23:45.599
Goodnight.

23:48.729 --> 23:49.602
Goodnight.

24:02.242 --> 24:04.286
So, what's your plan?

24:05.620 --> 24:06.620
You got one?

24:08.957 --> 24:10.749
No.

24:10.751 --> 24:11.791
You want butter?

24:11.793 --> 24:13.334
Yeah.

24:13.336 --> 24:15.295
You want a job?

24:15.297 --> 24:16.922
No.

24:16.924 --> 24:19.757
I mean I'm not asking
because I need the money.

24:19.759 --> 24:22.345
I'll feed you, that's
not the problem.

24:23.930 --> 24:26.181
Listen, retirement's
a beautiful thing,

24:26.183 --> 24:27.183
don't get me wrong.

24:28.310 --> 24:29.977
It's just that,

24:29.979 --> 24:34.230
you really gotta fill
your days, you know.

24:34.232 --> 24:36.817
I figured that out
after Ann passed away.

24:36.819 --> 24:38.903
Before that all I was
doing was walking around,

24:38.905 --> 24:39.905
bored and drunk.

24:42.532 --> 24:44.324
Had scotch at noon,

24:44.326 --> 24:45.950
and then 10,

24:45.952 --> 24:47.994
eight o' clock with breakfast.

24:47.996 --> 24:49.788
Sounds a good idea to me.

24:49.790 --> 24:51.122
Except it's not a good idea.

24:51.124 --> 24:54.002
Especially when it stops
you from filling your days.

24:55.212 --> 24:56.212
Okay.

24:57.965 --> 25:00.967
So, what's your plan?

25:04.805 --> 25:07.972
I recon I'll follow your lead.

25:07.974 --> 25:09.852
How do you spend a day?

25:12.020 --> 25:12.811
Well.

25:57.357 --> 25:58.943
It's a peaceful life.

26:00.777 --> 26:01.526
Fine.

26:45.990 --> 26:48.072
See this old timer, here?

26:48.074 --> 26:49.240
Huh?

26:49.242 --> 26:51.284
Guy across the
street, walking the dog.

26:51.286 --> 26:53.037
It's connected.

26:53.039 --> 26:54.329
To what?

26:54.331 --> 26:55.955
Armenian mafia.

26:55.957 --> 26:58.959
Or whatever they
call themselves.

26:58.961 --> 27:00.168
They're always
hanging out in front.

27:00.170 --> 27:02.670
Like a pack of dogs,
barking at each other,

27:02.672 --> 27:06.132
barbecuing strange
meats at all hours.

27:06.134 --> 27:07.675
They play poker right
on the front porch,

27:07.677 --> 27:09.969
and the cops don't
even bother them.

27:09.971 --> 27:13.017
Hollering like little
kids, fuckin nuisance.

27:13.934 --> 27:15.725
Drive like assholes,

27:15.727 --> 27:16.979
any speed they want.

27:17.855 --> 27:19.354
You hear that motorcycle yet?

27:19.356 --> 27:20.981
Oh yeah I heard that.

27:20.983 --> 27:22.690
Middle of the fucking
night, revving his engine.

27:22.692 --> 27:25.654
He stops at the same
house all the time.

27:27.656 --> 27:29.364
Here he comes with his dog.

27:29.366 --> 27:31.075
What kind of dog is that?

27:31.077 --> 27:33.035
I don't know why
don't you ask him?

27:33.037 --> 27:34.035
Sir!

27:34.037 --> 27:35.244
I was just joking.

27:35.246 --> 27:36.037
Hello sir.

27:36.039 --> 27:37.330
Yes?

27:37.332 --> 27:38.623
What kind of
dog do you got there?

27:38.625 --> 27:41.087
This little gentleman
is a lhasaapso.

27:42.671 --> 27:44.004
He's beautiful.

27:44.006 --> 27:45.632
I thank you on his behalf.

27:46.968 --> 27:48.218
What's your name, my friend?

27:49.177 --> 27:50.176
Who's asking?

27:51.429 --> 27:52.470
You look familiar to me.

27:52.472 --> 27:53.596
We know each other?

27:53.598 --> 27:55.059
Forgive me, I am Levon.

27:55.935 --> 27:56.935
Arthur.

28:02.273 --> 28:05.067
Friends call me Boe.

28:05.069 --> 28:06.234
Boe the thief.

28:07.112 --> 28:08.111
It is you.

28:08.113 --> 28:09.445
You guys know each other?

28:09.447 --> 28:11.364
We drank too much
ouzo one night,

28:11.366 --> 28:13.282
at one of my
brother's restaurants.

28:13.284 --> 28:14.659
He made him a lot of money.

28:14.661 --> 28:16.870
His name was on my
brother's tongue.

28:16.872 --> 28:17.871
You've been gone a long time,

28:17.873 --> 28:19.247
haven't you my bro.

28:19.249 --> 28:20.581
When did you come back to
the land of the living?

28:20.583 --> 28:22.208
A week ago.

28:22.210 --> 28:23.877
Welcome back my bro.

28:23.879 --> 28:25.006
Shan tula!

28:26.131 --> 28:27.881
I'm having you both for dinner.

28:27.883 --> 28:29.925
No it's alright, we
wouldn't want to impose.

28:29.927 --> 28:31.176
I insist.

28:31.178 --> 28:32.970
My wife, she makes
enough food for an army.

28:32.972 --> 28:34.345
Do you like lamb?

28:34.347 --> 28:35.638
That's alright, I
got a chicken in the oven.

28:35.640 --> 28:37.598
I love lamb.

28:37.600 --> 28:38.809
It is settled.

28:38.811 --> 28:40.226
We are having lamb,
drinking ouzo,

28:40.228 --> 28:42.311
and reminiscing
about the old days.

28:42.313 --> 28:43.856
Let me finish up with
the doggie business,

28:43.858 --> 28:45.106
I come back okay.

28:45.108 --> 28:46.235
Don't go anywhere.

28:48.195 --> 28:49.862
Hang up, I'll walk with you.

29:25.900 --> 29:27.192
Sorry to wake ya.

29:29.110 --> 29:31.071
How was dinner?

29:35.533 --> 29:38.117
That is a lovely family.

29:38.119 --> 29:39.160
Oh yeah.

29:39.162 --> 29:40.161
Oh yeah.

29:40.163 --> 29:41.206
Two little boys.

29:42.332 --> 29:43.790
A lovely,

29:43.792 --> 29:45.625
girl of 15.

29:45.627 --> 29:46.627
That's nice.

29:50.423 --> 29:53.633
My chicken is in the oven.

29:53.635 --> 29:54.675
You eat?

29:54.677 --> 29:55.846
Oh yeah, lots.

29:57.098 --> 29:58.933
Wife's name's Nora.

30:00.309 --> 30:01.309
Hell of a cook.

30:04.313 --> 30:05.311
Good lamb?

30:05.313 --> 30:06.313
And how.

30:08.275 --> 30:09.983
Lots of spice,

30:09.985 --> 30:13.321
they cook it real
fast on a high flame.

30:14.949 --> 30:17.115
Must be some kind of marinade.

30:17.117 --> 30:19.575
Yeah must be.

30:19.577 --> 30:20.577
Fine house.

30:21.454 --> 30:22.832
Big back yard.

30:24.290 --> 30:26.251
Bunch of room for
kids to run and play.

30:27.710 --> 30:34.258
He's also got a little
office down stairs.

30:34.260 --> 30:37.054
Lots of privacy, got his
own entrance and a patio.

30:38.138 --> 30:40.973
Levon took me out
there after dinner.

30:40.975 --> 30:42.392
Smokes, cigars.

30:43.894 --> 30:45.560
He's a proud man.

30:45.562 --> 30:46.352
A man of power,

30:46.354 --> 30:47.356
some might say.

30:48.731 --> 30:51.482
I'd say, careless.

30:51.484 --> 30:54.610
I mean, take a strange
dog like me into his home?

30:54.612 --> 30:57.322
Let me loose around
those little kids?

30:57.324 --> 31:00.242
What else is he careless with?

31:00.244 --> 31:02.243
I mean, did he leave it out
there in the open on purpose?

31:02.245 --> 31:04.163
Was I meant to see it?

31:04.165 --> 31:05.998
Is he just that stupid?

31:06.000 --> 31:07.582
See what?

31:07.584 --> 31:08.583
A bag.

31:08.585 --> 31:10.379
A big bag.

31:11.881 --> 31:13.546
It was zipped tight,

31:13.548 --> 31:15.173
but it didn't take
much imagination,

31:15.175 --> 31:17.218
to figure what was inside.

31:18.345 --> 31:20.304
Shapes, Artie.

31:20.306 --> 31:22.555
There are certain shapes
a man in my line of work,

31:22.557 --> 31:26.184
will recognize, bagged or no,

31:26.186 --> 31:28.147
26 years away or no.

31:28.981 --> 31:30.646
It had to be cash.

31:30.648 --> 31:32.773
I could smell it.

31:32.775 --> 31:34.358
20 grand at least in there,

31:34.360 --> 31:36.864
even if it was all
singles, which I doubt.

31:38.239 --> 31:41.033
There was guns too on top.

31:41.035 --> 31:42.035
I could see them.

31:43.244 --> 31:46.662
No safe, just a bag,

31:46.664 --> 31:49.126
out there, in the
middle of the desk.

31:50.127 --> 31:51.461
Quite a conversation piece,

31:54.423 --> 31:57.007
except I didn't make peep one.

32:13.441 --> 32:15.318
I could go in the
back with a shotgun.

32:16.527 --> 32:19.029
If that old gangster
got in my way,

32:19.031 --> 32:22.074
or any of those brat
offspring of his,

32:22.076 --> 32:25.827
or that fat cunny
of a wife of his?

32:25.829 --> 32:28.248
I'd blast their
goddamn faces off.

32:30.459 --> 32:33.461
Oh my God, that'd
be the real prize.

32:34.504 --> 32:37.546
To be myself once again.

32:37.548 --> 32:40.424
Go in like a wolf one last time.

32:40.426 --> 32:42.803
Raging fangs and claws.

32:42.805 --> 32:44.471
Come out with all that cash.

32:44.473 --> 32:46.848
Covered in blood,
pockets full of dough.

32:48.102 --> 32:49.352
That old time feeling.

32:52.647 --> 32:54.066
Is it wrong to still dream?

32:59.154 --> 33:01.320
I'll tell you straight, Artie,

33:01.322 --> 33:03.117
just between you and me.

33:03.909 --> 33:07.410
That girl I killed,

33:07.412 --> 33:09.331
on the job they
sent me away for?

33:11.332 --> 33:14.625
I'd kill her a
thousand times over.

33:14.627 --> 33:18.463
When I went up in front
of the parole board,

33:18.465 --> 33:19.797
they asked me,

33:19.799 --> 33:22.926
what I'd have done
different with my life?

33:22.928 --> 33:26.221
How I would have
lived it better?

33:26.223 --> 33:28.308
I told them what
they wanted to hear.

33:29.435 --> 33:30.435
The truth is,

33:32.438 --> 33:33.438
I'd have been worse.

33:34.523 --> 33:35.773
Much worse.

33:59.505 --> 34:00.922
You hear this Artie?

34:00.924 --> 34:02.424
You hear it?

34:02.426 --> 34:03.844
Levon and his bag!

34:06.387 --> 34:08.804
It's an old fashioned pickup.

34:08.806 --> 34:10.391
On a motorcycle, no less.

34:14.063 --> 34:16.355
All you'd need is a pistol,

34:16.357 --> 34:19.234
a mask, good escape route,

34:21.360 --> 34:23.110
and a little nerve.

35:11.995 --> 35:13.454
Oh, shit.

35:14.873 --> 35:16.498
What's the matter?

35:16.500 --> 35:18.751
I can't get the
Chrysler building right.

35:20.254 --> 35:21.880
Looks like
New York to me.

35:22.881 --> 35:24.591
How's your crossword puzzle?

35:27.010 --> 35:28.885
Nearly done.

35:28.887 --> 35:29.803
Good.

35:29.805 --> 35:31.471
You want eggplant for dinner?

35:31.473 --> 35:32.514
Sure.

35:49.657 --> 35:52.409
Hey Boe, I left a
half a turkey sandwich,

35:52.411 --> 35:53.952
for ya in the kitchen.

35:53.954 --> 35:54.954
Alright,

35:55.663 --> 35:56.454
okay.

35:56.456 --> 35:58.206
I'll see ya tomorrow.

37:01.604 --> 37:03.313
You never seen that picture?

37:03.315 --> 37:04.105
No.

37:04.107 --> 37:05.689
Well it's fabulous.

37:05.691 --> 37:09.569
Glen Ford plays this bad guy,

37:09.571 --> 37:10.862
turns out to be this
charming son of a bitch.

37:13.741 --> 37:15.242
it's a classic.

37:16.161 --> 37:17.578
We'll get it from the Net flick.

37:18.579 --> 37:19.664
Yeah hello.

37:21.583 --> 37:22.832
Yeah this is Artie Twine.

37:22.834 --> 37:23.834
Whose this?

37:25.753 --> 37:26.753
Yeah one sec.

37:28.090 --> 37:29.339
Says he's your grandson.

37:29.341 --> 37:30.673
You got a grandson?

37:30.675 --> 37:32.217
Maybe.

37:32.219 --> 37:33.717
How'd he find me?

37:33.719 --> 37:35.180
How'd you get my number?

37:38.809 --> 37:40.642
He says he gave his
I.D. to the prison,

37:40.644 --> 37:42.602
and they gave him my info.

37:44.314 --> 37:45.105
What does he want?

37:54.032 --> 37:55.991
Yeah,

37:55.993 --> 37:57.951
Yeah, this is he.

37:57.953 --> 38:00.745
And you're Frank's son right?

38:00.747 --> 38:02.205
Freddie?

38:02.207 --> 38:06.334
Yeah, that was my father's name.

38:06.336 --> 38:09.296
I hope you've had better
luck with it than he did.

38:09.298 --> 38:10.671
So what's going on?

38:35.699 --> 38:36.948
What a cute couple hey.

38:36.950 --> 38:37.907
How you doin?

38:37.909 --> 38:38.825
Mr. Twine?

38:38.827 --> 38:39.826
No, no, no, no, no, no.

38:39.828 --> 38:40.618
Not Mr. Twine.

38:40.620 --> 38:41.786
It's Artie, Artie.

38:41.788 --> 38:42.954
Come on, come on, come on in.

38:42.956 --> 38:43.746
Boe's washing up.

38:43.748 --> 38:44.791
Boe!

38:47.794 --> 38:49.002
It smells delicious in here.

38:49.004 --> 38:50.295
Oh thank you, dear.

38:50.297 --> 38:51.754
Uh, Artie, this
is my fiancee Robin.

38:51.756 --> 38:54.591
Oh hello fiance Robin.

38:54.593 --> 38:55.925
Thanks a million
for having us.

38:55.927 --> 38:57.552
Oh please please,

38:57.554 --> 38:58.178
come on, we're gonna have
a fabulous dinner here.

38:58.180 --> 38:59.180
Hi.

39:01.975 --> 39:03.391
Hi!

39:08.357 --> 39:10.148
Dad always had
some scam going.

39:10.150 --> 39:12.108
There was a Christmas eve I was,

39:12.110 --> 39:13.652
eight or nine, he had
me with him selling,

39:13.654 --> 39:14.735
a truck load of televisions.

39:14.737 --> 39:16.863
I helped him load
it and everything.

39:16.865 --> 39:20.075
Got a little Schwarzenegger
here, lifting televisions.

39:20.077 --> 39:21.869
They were actually just boxes.

39:21.871 --> 39:24.245
The thing of it was he had
all these brand new boxes but,

39:24.247 --> 39:25.706
we didn't have any televisions.

39:26.876 --> 39:28.291
Where'd you get the boxes?

39:28.293 --> 39:31.878
He raided the dumpster of
news station, in Studio City.

39:31.880 --> 39:33.380
Apparently he'd been
eyeing the place,

39:33.382 --> 39:35.340
to nab it for some equipment,

39:35.342 --> 39:36.633
but it was like a fortress,

39:36.635 --> 39:37.885
there was cameras
everywhere and shit.

39:37.887 --> 39:39.427
One day though, he
sees they're dumping,

39:39.429 --> 39:41.763
all these brand new boxes,
and he gets an idea.

39:41.765 --> 39:43.390
That's so cool.

39:43.392 --> 39:45.766
He must have been broke,
because looking back on it now,

39:45.768 --> 39:47.727
it was a hell of a risk.

39:47.729 --> 39:50.689
We hooked up with this
guy in Orange County.

39:50.691 --> 39:52.065
Dad shows him the
truck full of boxes,

39:52.067 --> 39:53.650
everything's on the up and up.

39:53.652 --> 39:56.069
We put cinder blocks in
the ones along the outside,

39:56.071 --> 39:57.904
so the weight felt right,

39:57.906 --> 40:00.740
and in one we put our own TV
from the goddamn living room.

40:00.742 --> 40:02.783
It wasn't even the same
